bug.short_desc: All attachment sections should also display the camera icon to select "Attach Screenshot..."

long_desc.thetext:
In the same way as e.g. the JIRA connector does, all connectors (Bugzilla, Trac etc) should display the camera icon besides the "Attach..." icon in the top right corner of the attachment section.
Will attach a screen shot to demonstrate this.

Thanks for the request. It makes sense to me and should be straight forward to implement.
Thanks, Steffen. Looking forward to save on extra click...
BTW, my German umlauts are broken again. With Tasktop Bugzilla this works fine. What could be the reason?
Can you check the charset setting for Eclipse.org repository? It should be set to UTF-8.

(In reply to comment #5) > Can you check the charset setting for Eclipse.org repository? It should be set > to UTF-8.
Yes, I changed it back to UTF-8 (was at ISO-8859-1 before) before I published this comment. But for some reason this was not picked up.
Now I restarted Eclipse -- you will see whether it helped.
Hmmm... Obviously not. My Eclipse is using ISO-8859-1, but with Tasktop it works. No idea.
Thanks, Steffen. This issue also appears if using the web site. Somehow the encoding is mangled from the global Eclipse account page. See bug 374895.
Frank, do you have time to look into this? The main thing to be aware of is that the icon needs to be 12x12 to fit into the toolbar.

Done!
If you think we need an better icon, please feel free to reopen!
